&lt;p&gt;Therapy Assistant Practitioner Band 4 - Medical QEQM&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to work alongside experienced clinicians on the medical wards at Queen Elizabeth Queen Mother Hospital, Margate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be able to provide support to the multidisciplinary team on the Medical wards in the day to day assessments of clients and delivery of treatment programmes. The Band 4 role will also involve the timely planning of discharge and referral to onward community services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Band 4 Assistant Practitioner you will be part of a well-established Therapy team of Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists with grades ranging from Band 3 to Band 8a. The well-staffed teams work generically, providing high quality care through effective team work. A positive and organised approach to rehabilitation is essential. Good communication skills and commitment to team working within a safe, empathetic and supportive environment are also needed. The post holder also needs to be able to drive or be able to travel between sites or to patients homes across East Kent efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular supervision, competency training, performance reviews and Continued Personal Development are actively encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracy Maringer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Band 7 OT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:tracy.maringer@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:07795 834229&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Siobhan Fairclough, Therapy Site Lead Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother Hospital siobhanfairclough@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
